        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:51PM EDT by NWS State College PA</headline>
        <description>Strong thunderstorms moving across the area early this evening
will create...

* Wind gusts up to 45 mph during the period of heaviest rain.
* Hail up to pea size.
* A 15 minute period of heavy rain will occur, totaling between
one quarter and one half of an inch.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Most of the storms will gradually weaken as they near a line from
Coudersport to Driftwood, Philipsburg, Ebensburg and Johnstown
between 730 and 745 pm.

Continue to monitor local radio stations and available television
stations for additional information and possible warnings from
your National Weather Service.
</description>
